description:
&lt;p&gt;The Performance Analysis Team is an analytical service supporting NHS England and NHS Improvement national and regional teams by providing information and analysis to inform policy and operational decisions. Our service spans the whole analytical pipeline, from data development and data collection, through to reporting and bespoke analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example projects include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modelling to inform Spending Review discussions with the Department of Health and Her Majesty’s Treasury&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In-depth analysis to shape the Long-Term&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan Collecting and assuring plans to ensure that local health systems can deliver the care their patients need within the resources they have available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitoring in-year delivery and working with local health systems to improve performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Performance and Analysis team operate from Leeds, London and regional offices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware it may take longer than usual for us to contact you regarding your application, due to current workload pressures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Performance and Analysis team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: england.performanceanalysisteam@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please indicate what role you are enquiring about in your email.&lt;/p&gt;
